        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 3:27PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Lake Wister State Park, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Wister...                         Lake Wister State Park...
Heavener...                       Howe...
Hodgen...                         Summerfield...
Fanshawe...                       Poteau...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
southeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
